Progressive Underground (2014) 

                     Progressive House | Armada Music Holland

                320 kbps | MP3 | unmixed | 2014 | 01:30:53 | 211 Mb


Take a step back to the roots of progressive house - when ambient textures, smooth grooves, deep bass, and refined sonic architecture reigned supreme. The underground is back in style, bringing thought-provoking tracks that are guaranteed to send your mind on an incredible journey. Ross Couch's 'Enlightenment' sets the tone of the release, an opener followed capably by the iconic Eelke Klein. Deetron brings his modulating remix to the table, and genre-pioneer Medway takes us on a trip through space and time. For a seamless experience that rewards a pair of great headphones, dive deep into the 'Progressive Underground'. Hit play at the start, and let it ride all the way Grum's intense finish. Welcome to the Progressive Underground!
